Uniformity	#16.	 in harmony with &c. (agreeing). always, invariably, without exception, without fail, unfailingly, never otherwise
Generality	#78.	 always, for better for worse
Time	#106.	 hourly, always
Perpetuity	#112.	 always, ever, evermore, aye
Qualification	#469.	 contingent &c. (uncertain). Adv. provided, provided that, provided always
Habit	#613.	 always &c. (uniformly). as usual, as is one's wont, as things go, as the world goes, as the sparks fly upwards
Success	#731.	 The race is not always to the swift, nor the battle The race is not always to the swift, nor the battle to the strong, but that's the way to bet" [Mark Twain].
